                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Catalogue no. 16; Nelson collection no. N270.  Psenchonsis, son of Teos is Muhs&amp;apos; Taxpayer 15.  1/4 silver (kite) or 3 obols is the price of 1 1/2 kotulai or 0.41 liter of oil.  The scribe Esminis was responsible for many other price of oil receipts from Thebes between years 30 and 38 of Ptolemy II.  (See additional OIM ostraca.)</note>
